==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Erysipelothrix
<hw>Er`y*sip"e*lo*thrix</hw>
<pr>(⟦ecr⟧r`⟦icr⟧*s⟦icr⟧p"⟦esl⟧*l⟦ait⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[see
<er>erysipelas</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Microbiol.)</fld> <def>a genus of
non-motile, rod-shaped Gram-positive bacteria of the family
<fam>Corynebacteriaceae</fam>. They are facultatively anaerobic and
produce acid but no gas from glucose. Members of this genus are
parasitic on fish, birds, and mammals, including man. The type species
of the genus, <spn>Erysipelothrix rhusiopathiae</spn>, causes
erysipeloid in man.</def> <au>Stedman</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Erysipelous</ent>⟦br⟧
